# Grantless environment overrides. Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) to use.
# Every value here is an OPTIONAL, overridable convenience — none is required and
# none confers special status on any relay (Grantless prime directive).

# Override the shipped DEFAULT relay (a forker repoints Grantless at their own
# relay without editing code). When unset, the default is wss://relay.grantless.org
# — a plain, overridable convenience, never privileged.
# VITE_DEFAULT_RELAY=wss://relay.example.com

# Point the app at a specific relay on startup (custom mode — overrides the default
# set entirely). When unset, the app uses its normal default relay set (the
# RelaySelector UI still works either way). `npm run dev` defaults this to the local
# strfry that `npm run seed` fills; set it here to browse a different relay instead.
# VITE_RELAY_URL=ws://127.0.0.1:7787

# Optional curator allow-list for the curator picker, as a comma-separated list
# of npub… or 64-char hex pubkeys. These are MERGED with the curators discovered
# on the relay (anyone who published a grantless-applicants list) — they are a
# plain convenience, never privileged, and the default (unset) is discovery only.
# VITE_GRANTLESS_CURATORS=npub1xxxx...,npub1yyyy...

# Optional operator pubkey(s), as a comma-separated list of npub… or 64-char hex.
# Whoever is logged in as one of these sees a read-only "operator helper panel" at
# /admin listing projects that look stuck (creator vouched by no curator; or no
# arbiter assigned) — convenience queries to help people whose crowdfunding isn't
# active. It grants NO special capability (every query is a public read anyone could
# run) and is NOT access control — just UI decluttering. Unset (the default) hides
# the panel and its nav link for everyone. A forker sets their own pubkey here.
# VITE_GRANTLESS_OPERATOR=npub1xxxx...
